"The steer, who to the yoke was bred to bow (Studious of tillage, and the crooked plough), Falls down and dies ; and, dying, spews a tlood Of foamy madness, mix’'d with clotted blood. The clown, who, cursing Providence, repines, His mournful fellow from the team disjoins ; With many a groan forsakes his fruitless care, And in the' unfinish’d farrow leaves the share. The pining steer, no shades of lofty woods,"